abstract: Stocks decline slightly as negotiations over Greek debt stall.
lead_paragraph: Health care stocks rose sharply after the Supreme Court upheld the Affordable Care Act’s subsidies. But investors continued to monitor a stalemate in Greece.

headline.main: Health Care Shares Jump, but Market Slides Back
headline.print_headline: Greece Worries Weigh on Wall St., but Health Shares Jump After Court Ruling
